Following the ongoing security challenges in some parts of the North, the Kebbi State Governor, Atiku Abubakar Bagudu, has summoned security chiefs and traditional rulers to a meeting, with a view to tackling the security situations in the state. Briefing our correspondent on Thursday, at the Government House, Birnin Kebbi, the Chief Press Secretary (CPS) to the governor, Alhaji Muâ€™azu Dakingari, said the meeting was aimed at how to protect lives and properties of the people. He said that Kebbi State was known as the most peaceful state in the country and as such the governor has promised to continue to maintain peace and harmony enjoyed by the people for a long time.